 It can.. but only if you put the interactions window next to the
 definitions window by checking a box in preferences->general. It might
 be nice to split the definitions pane so you get two windows side by
 side even when the interactions window is below the definitions window.
 
 Having gone through this code just recently I don't think its a hard
 change to make. Maybe add a new option to the View menu like
   * Split horizontally
   * Split vertically
 
 ?
 
